children.name: Earth is the only planet known to support life, with vast oceans, lush forests, and diverse ecosystems. It's just the right distance from the Sun to maintain temperatures suitable for life as we know it. From towering mountains to deep ocean trenches, Earth is a planet full of wonders waiting to be explored.

children.name: Venus is often called Earth's "sister planet" because they are similar in size and composition. However, Venus has a thick atmosphere made mostly of carbon dioxide, which traps heat and makes it the hottest planet in the Solar System. Its surface is shrouded in dense clouds of sulfuric acid, hiding its rocky terrain from view.

children.name: Saturn is famous for its dazzling rings, made up of countless icy particles ranging in size from tiny grains to large chunks. Beneath its rings, Saturn is a gas giant similar to Jupiter, with swirling storms and a complex atmosphere. Saturn has more than 80 moons, with Titan being the largest and most intriguing, with its thick atmosphere and methane lakes.
